A vintage-style travel poster composition featuring a stylized world map with glowing pin markers on Melbourne, Singapore, Manila, and Shanghai, connected by sweeping dotted flight path lines in warm golden and burnt orange tones. In the foreground, a leather briefcase and vintage boarding passes are artfully arranged. The color palette evokes 1960s airline advertisements with muted teals, creams, and rich burgundy accents. The map has an aged paper texture with subtle fold creases, and small iconic landmarks (Sydney Opera House silhouette, Marina Bay outline) emerge subtly near their respective cities. Warm ambient lighting creates a sense of adventure and professional purpose.
